<module status="bronze">
  <h>-(e)ag</h>
  <p><g>-(e)ag</g> is a suffix used to create feminine <a href="?xx=nouns/derived_common_nouns"
      >derived common nouns</a> from adjectives and from other nouns.</p>
  <section id="adj">
    <h>de-adjectival</h>
    <p>Examples derived from adjectives – <ul>
        <li><g>sleamhainn</g>
          <adj/>
          <en>slippery</en> ⇒ <g>sleamhnag</g>
          <fem/>
          <en>slide (for playing on)</en></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>
  <section id="nouns">
    <h>denominal</h>
    <p>Examples derived from common nouns – <ul>
        <li><g>braid</g>
          <fem/>
          <en>theft</en> ⇒ <g>bradag</g>
          <fem/>
          <en>thievish girl</en></li>
        <li><g>rionn</g>
          <masc/>
          <en>star [archaic]</en> ⇒ <a href="?gd=rionnag"><g>rionnag</g></a>
          <fem/>
          <en>star</en></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>
  <section id="other">
    <h>other</h>
    <p>Diminutives of unclear derivation – <ul>
        <li><a href="?gd=faoileag"><g>faoileag</g></a>
          <fem/>
          <en>seagull</en></li>
        <li><a href="?gd=sgalag"><g>sgalag</g></a>
          <fem/>
          <en>farm servant</en></li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </section>
</module>
